The paper discusses the measurement of user influence on Twitter, which is a social networking service with millions of users. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of different metrics and algorithms to measure influence, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Retrieval). The use of content analysis and the consideration of specific topics also suggest the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of computational complexity, which falls under the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of cybersecurity in the context of Twitter, which suggests the sub-category of cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
